  "title": "R&D Intern",
  "description": "<p>**Ideally able to commit to at least a 4 months attachment**</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· To assist in performing new product development from ingredient sourcing, laboratory and kitchen trials to commercialization, focusing especially in sauces.</p>\n<p>· To support in conducting sensory evaluation and approval of new and/or alternative raw materials.</p>\n<p>· To conceptualize new and innovative products.</p>\n<p>· Ensure all product creation complies with customer, government and legal regulatory requirements within the country of use.</p>\n<p>· To support in developing innovative solutions to help grow and value-add to customers’ requirements, ensuring that any solutions provided are within the stipulated cost parameters and manufacturing capability.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p>\n<p>· Candidate should ideally be pursuing a Diploma/Degree in Food Science/Biotechnology or related courses.</p>\n<p>· Meticulous and well-organized, able to work independently</p>\n<p>· Willingness to learn and a team player</p>\n<p>· Proficient in MS Office</p>\n<p>· Comfortable working in a food manufacturing environment</p>",
